description:
ABSTRACT&nbsp; 
Information Assurance, in short, is called as IA. This is responsible for securing information&nbsp; 
systems &nbsp;and &nbsp;computing. &nbsp;The &nbsp;term &nbsp;holds &nbsp;the &nbsp;highest &nbsp;degree &nbsp;of &nbsp;security &nbsp;related &nbsp;affairs. &nbsp;In&nbsp; 
generally Computer Security considered as a branch and area of security but now apart from&nbsp; 
this, Information Security, IT Security, and Information Assurance considered as important.&nbsp; 
And &nbsp;among &nbsp;these, &nbsp;security &nbsp;related &nbsp;domain &nbsp;Information &nbsp;Assurance &nbsp;treated &nbsp;as &nbsp;broader &nbsp;and&nbsp; 
interdisciplinary. Moreover, this Information Assurance holds all the areas and dealing of IT&nbsp; 
Security &nbsp;and &nbsp;Information &nbsp;Security &nbsp;but &nbsp;additionally, &nbsp;it &nbsp;is &nbsp;responsible &nbsp;for &nbsp;the &nbsp;designing,&nbsp; 
development of policies, regulation and guidelines of security related projects /proposal, etc.&nbsp; 
And &nbsp;among &nbsp;the &nbsp;administrative &nbsp;and &nbsp;protocol &nbsp;related &nbsp;affairs &nbsp;Security &nbsp;Content &nbsp;Automation&nbsp; 
Protocol treated as important. In short, it is called as SCAP. It is a kind of method for using&nbsp; 
specific &nbsp;standards &nbsp;for &nbsp;the &nbsp;purpose &nbsp;of &nbsp;enabling &nbsp;vulnerability &nbsp;management &nbsp;systems &nbsp;in &nbsp;an&nbsp; 
automated way for the measurement as well as policy compliance assessment regarding &nbsp;the&nbsp; 
systems &nbsp;inbuilt &nbsp;in a company or &nbsp;institutions; &nbsp;that may &nbsp;include &nbsp;IT company or may not be.&nbsp; 
This is a conceptual paper, initially, it has discussed with the areas of Information Assurance&nbsp; 
but gradually it has described about the Security Content Automation Protocol; including its&nbsp; 
aim and objectives, versions, etc. paper mentioned all the areas in short and simple sense. &nbsp;

